WEBVTT

00:01.734 --> 00:03.405
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:03.469 --> 00:07.420
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:07.474 --> 00:09.324
the police
who investigate crime

00:09.376 --> 00:12.146
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:12.212 --> 00:13.822
These are their stories.

00:14.915 --> 00:16.785
If you would come home
when you said you would...

00:16.850 --> 00:18.490
Oh, it's my fault
the train broke down?

00:18.552 --> 00:21.762
Well, you know I don't like
to walk her by myself.

00:21.822 --> 00:25.772
I'll tell Amtrak. Look, next
time you get to clean the rug.

00:26.226 --> 00:29.826
Will. Look at him
check those cars.

00:30.063 --> 00:32.012
He's not doing anything.

00:32.064 --> 00:34.665
How many times are we gonna let
these punks steal our radios?

00:34.735 --> 00:37.875
Well, what're you gonna do,
sic lamb chop on him?

00:37.938 --> 00:40.608
Come on, honey, he could be dangerous.
We shouldn't have to live like...

00:40.674 --> 00:42.024
(GLASS SHATTERING)

00:42.075 --> 00:45.245
That's it.
Call 911. Hey!

00:45.946 --> 00:47.426
(DIALING PHONE)

00:55.589 --> 00:57.399
I mean, look at this.

00:59.560 --> 01:00.770
Oh. My God!

01:00.827 --> 01:02.167
(WOMAN GASPING)

01:03.630 --> 01:05.540
(SIRENS WAILING)

01:07.100 --> 01:10.170
So no ID?
Blonde, maybe 35.

01:10.237 --> 01:13.617
We ran the plates. Car's registered to
Dobson Enterprises, whatever that is.

01:13.674 --> 01:16.424
How bad was she?
Alive. Barely.

01:16.476 --> 01:19.116
Paramedics said a bullet went into
her head and didn't come out.

01:19.179 --> 01:21.219
That's him! That's the man!

01:21.782 --> 01:24.292
Spotted him
running across Broadway.

01:24.351 --> 01:26.591
Three Blaupunkts
and a Delco in his bag.

01:26.653 --> 01:28.563
You know what car radio
thieves call this street?

01:28.622 --> 01:29.932
Audio Warehouse.

01:29.990 --> 01:31.160
MONTERO: No gun, though.

01:31.224 --> 01:33.234
Well, we'll organize a search
from here to Broadway.

01:33.293 --> 01:36.003
Yo, I didn't shoot nobody.
There was no shot.

01:36.063 --> 01:37.273
Well, maybe
you just didn't hear it.

01:37.331 --> 01:38.971
No, it was quiet.
I would've heard it.

01:39.032 --> 01:40.672
JEROME: Man, the lady
was bagged when I got here.

01:40.734 --> 01:43.944
Yeah? She break the window, too?
Maybe the guy that done her.

01:44.004 --> 01:46.284
One of those carjackers.
Take him in.

01:46.340 --> 01:48.120
JEROME: What's up?
For the radios.

01:50.644 --> 01:52.184
First the shooter,
then this guy.

01:52.245 --> 01:54.085
People were lining up
to get to this lady.

01:54.147 --> 01:55.817
If she was shot
in a safer neighborhood,

01:55.882 --> 01:58.062
we wouldn't have found her
till tomorrow.

