02:46.800 --> 02:50.210
DAVID: The bullet entered two inches from the
eye, tore through the left frontal lobe,

02:50.270 --> 02:53.620
ricocheted off the back of the skull
down through the occipital lobe.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.094
Ended up in the cerebellum.

02:55.142 --> 02:56.992
Is there any chance
we'll be able to talk to her?

02:57.044 --> 02:59.754
She's breathing, but cortical
function is limited.

02:59.813 --> 03:02.293
On the Glasgow Coma Scale
she scores a four.

03:02.349 --> 03:05.989
And that's not good? That
lamp would score a three.

03:06.620 --> 03:08.660
There's a call
for Detective Briscoe.

03:09.489 --> 03:11.659
There are also abrasions
on her neck.

03:11.725 --> 03:14.465
Is that consistent with
having a necklace ripped off?

03:14.528 --> 03:15.528
I'd say so.

03:17.330 --> 03:20.570
What about those bruises there?
Old ones.

03:21.568 --> 03:25.518
How old? I'm not sure.
They were healing.

03:25.772 --> 03:29.022
They tracked the owner of the car.
Mr. Michael Dobson.

03:29.810 --> 03:32.520
Let's go tell him
how she saved his radio.

03:32.846 --> 03:33.846
Thanks, Doc.

03:37.584 --> 03:39.434
SUSANNAH: Well, how do I
know you're the police?

03:39.486 --> 03:41.226
(SIREN WAILING)

03:41.555 --> 03:42.655
(HORNS HONKING)

03:42.722 --> 03:43.932
Higher.

03:46.693 --> 03:48.203
(GATE BUZZING)

03:52.099 --> 03:54.549
I'm sorry, but I'm taking
care of two kids here.

03:54.601 --> 03:57.411
You the babysitter?
Yeah. Part-time.

03:58.939 --> 04:02.679
Did... Did something happen? Well,
I'm afraid there's been an accident.

04:04.144 --> 04:07.324
Who's she?
Mrs. Dobson.

04:07.380 --> 04:10.990
Yeah, and that's Mr. Dobson
and Jessica and Jeremy.

04:11.318 --> 04:13.158
Did... Did something
happen to her?

04:13.754 --> 04:15.464
We're gonna need to speak
to Mr. Dobson, honey.

04:15.522 --> 04:16.732
Do you know where he is?

04:16.790 --> 04:19.200
He... He's at Ha-Ha.
Ha-Ha?

04:19.259 --> 04:22.599
It's the comedy club. He owns it.
He works nights.

04:23.697 --> 04:28.607
So the guy's 102 and the wife
is 98 and the attorney says,

04:28.668 --> 04:31.808
"If you both, you know, hated
each other this much for so long,"

04:31.872 --> 04:33.852
"you know, why'd you wait
till now to get a divorce?"

04:33.907 --> 04:37.047
And the wife says, "We were waiting
for the kids to die. You see."

04:37.110 --> 04:38.380
Two, three, four.

04:38.445 --> 04:41.915
Oh! Look it here. It's always nice
to see the bridge-and-tunnel crowd.

04:41.982 --> 04:43.722
Tell me guys,
does Ward Cleaver know

04:43.784 --> 04:45.894
that you've borrowed
his sports jackets?

04:45.952 --> 04:47.832
Lucky for this guy
the audience isn't armed.

04:47.888 --> 04:52.458
I told you 20 times, these jerks
get one drink before they go on.

04:52.526 --> 04:54.466
One free drink.
One drink, period.

04:54.528 --> 04:55.628
Now,
if you can't remember that,

04:55.695 --> 04:57.295
I'm gonna have to get someone
who speaks English.

04:57.364 --> 04:59.284
Mr. Dobson?
What?

04:59.332 --> 05:01.642
I'm Detective Logan.
This is Detective Briscoe.

05:01.701 --> 05:02.771
(EXCLAIMING)

05:03.904 --> 05:09.054
Well, if you've got an act, you're too late.
It's about your wife, sir.

05:09.276 --> 05:12.746
I'm afraid she's been shot.
What?

05:12.813 --> 05:15.193
We think it happened
during a robbery.

05:18.351 --> 05:22.771
How... How is she? She's
alive, but it's very serious.

05:23.123 --> 05:27.303
Oh, God. I told her it was too
dangerous to be working at night.

05:27.360 --> 05:30.000
She was working?
Some half-assed newspaper.

05:30.063 --> 05:32.673
Where is she?
Manhattan General.

05:33.600 --> 05:37.880
I've gotta call the babysitter.
Give me the phone!

05:43.743 --> 05:45.483
I hope Sandra makes it back.

05:45.545 --> 05:48.575
She's the only adult on my
staff who can do the job.

05:48.648 --> 05:52.148
Present company excepted, of course.
I own the paper.

05:52.219 --> 05:53.819
Everybody else is kids
on their way up,

05:53.887 --> 05:56.867
who want to turn every human
interest story into Watergate,

05:56.923 --> 05:59.703
or old-timers who couldn't
make it in the big leagues.

05:59.759 --> 06:01.499
But Mrs. Dobson could?

06:01.962 --> 06:05.712
Masters in Journalism from Columbia,
two years on the Fairfield Ledger.

06:05.765 --> 06:06.795
Very strong clips.

06:06.867 --> 06:09.777
No offense meant,
but what's she doing here?

06:10.170 --> 06:13.480
Because I have the good fortune of
being a stop on the mommy track.

06:14.107 --> 06:17.017
When Sandra had kids, she
didn't try and have it all.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.947
She stayed home
for seven years.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.063
I guess
she missed her career, huh?

06:21.114 --> 06:23.794
Enough to come back as one of
my neighborhood columnists.

06:23.850 --> 06:26.560
A few hours a week,
her choice of which hours.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.660
The Times isn't so flexible.

06:28.722 --> 06:31.262
Which part of the neighborhood
was she in last night?

06:31.324 --> 06:34.864
Tribeca. Citizens
advisory board meeting.

06:34.928 --> 06:37.408
She took a thermos
of strong coffee.

06:37.464 --> 06:39.884
How late was she there?
Not very.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.810
She told me she was going to see
somebody on Riverside Drive.

06:44.404 --> 06:47.654
So Mrs. Dobson worked part-time
for the Westside Sentinel.

06:47.707 --> 06:50.237
She was covering a community board
meeting that ended at 9:00,

06:50.310 --> 06:53.290
we found her at midnight. Anything
exciting happen at the meeting?

06:53.346 --> 06:56.156
They voted to spend 400 bucks
on guard rails.

06:56.216 --> 06:58.746
Yeah, to keep the dogs
from pooping on the trees.

06:58.818 --> 07:00.418
We're working on carjackers.

07:00.487 --> 07:04.257
You know, who likes BMWs, who
likes to work Riverside Drive...

07:04.324 --> 07:05.534
Who uses a gun.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.632
Yeah, well, I think we ought
to look a little wider.

07:07.694 --> 07:10.404
BRISCOE: At what, angry dogs?
No.

07:10.463 --> 07:14.143
Mr. Dobson. Mrs. Dobson
had a few old bruises.

07:14.200 --> 07:16.440
It looks like a carjacking.

07:16.503 --> 07:19.283
If it's a carjacking, how come
the shooter didn't take the car?

07:19.339 --> 07:21.549
He forgot or he just
can't drive a stick?

07:22.375 --> 07:24.815
Go see what Forensics got
from the vehicle.

07:26.513 --> 07:31.863
Gunpowder residue on the headrest. A half-circle.
The other half's on her head.

07:31.918 --> 07:33.828
So she was shot at close range.

07:33.887 --> 07:36.957
Where were the keys?
On the floor. There.

07:37.824 --> 07:40.274
Like she dropped them when
someone stuck a gun in her face.

07:40.327 --> 07:42.897
So she's sitting in the car
with the door open...

07:42.963 --> 07:48.783
Or she opens the door, she gets in,
she starts to close the door...

07:48.835 --> 07:51.675
Somebody comes along, bang.

07:52.872 --> 07:54.852
Why?
I don't know.

07:54.908 --> 07:58.378
She resisted, his finger
slipped, maybe he's a psycho.

07:58.778 --> 08:01.818
Not so psycho he didn't grab
the purse, grab her jewelry.

08:02.983 --> 08:05.363
Isn't anybody gonna ask me
about fingerprints?

08:06.820 --> 08:10.100
Lean in, pull off my jewelry
Come on.

08:11.324 --> 08:13.304
See? Where your hand is.

08:13.793 --> 08:17.763
We got a backward-facing, left-hand
palm print and partial thumb.

08:18.531 --> 08:20.371
Michael Dobson, the husband.

08:20.433 --> 08:23.383
What, you just happen to have his
fingerprints on hand for comparison?

08:23.436 --> 08:24.466
No.

08:24.537 --> 08:26.737
I had them pulled off his
liquor license application

08:26.806 --> 08:29.046
and sent over just for fun.

08:29.609 --> 08:32.519
Look, he owns the car. He
could've been in it every day.

08:32.578 --> 08:35.859
Then his prints would be on the
dashboard, the steering wheel.

08:35.914 --> 08:37.215
They're not.

08:37.283 --> 08:38.563
Just this.

08:39.085 --> 08:41.784
Now either the guy did a
handstand on the armrest,

08:41.855 --> 08:44.495
or he leaned in
to pull something out.

08:44.924 --> 08:48.964
So what? Maybe he reached in for
groceries, for a joke book.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.869
What, and there'd be
no other prints?

08:50.930 --> 08:53.970
Well, maybe she got the car
washed and they missed the seats.

08:54.034 --> 08:58.814
Kiss me. Mrs. Dobson's purse. Fresh
out of a garbage can on 96th Street.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.872
No money, no credit cards.

09:01.274 --> 09:06.054
Eye drops, lipstick,
notebook, comb...

09:07.714 --> 09:11.894
Well, it's her notes
on the dog poop debate.

09:12.485 --> 09:17.365
Page headed "Boxes?" with a question
mark and then a list of bank branches.

09:17.424 --> 09:19.564
So she was looking
to rent a safe deposit box?

09:19.626 --> 09:22.696
The branches are all on the East Side.
Nowhere near her apartment.

09:22.762 --> 09:24.612
Yeah, but they are
near her husband's club.

09:24.664 --> 09:26.704
Well, maybe she was gonna
rent a box for her husband.

09:26.766 --> 09:30.006
More likely looking for a box
rented by her husband.

09:30.070 --> 09:32.210
You own a cash business
like a comedy club,

09:32.272 --> 09:35.552
maybe you skim off some cash,
hide it from the IRS.

09:35.608 --> 09:37.248
BRISCOE: Or from his wife.

09:37.310 --> 09:39.920
And if she suspected and was
thinking about divorce,

09:39.979 --> 09:41.549
she'd want to track down
where that box is

09:41.614 --> 09:43.064
before she serves him
with the papers.

09:43.116 --> 09:45.386
Otherwise she can kiss
that cash goodbye.

09:45.452 --> 09:46.522
Speaking of divorce...

09:46.586 --> 09:49.086
Yeah, how were the Dobsons
getting along?

09:50.423 --> 09:52.933
I'd be waiting outside
their front door sometimes,

09:52.992 --> 09:56.632
and I would hear him
screaming like a lunatic.

09:56.996 --> 10:01.566
And... And then he would come to the
door and he would be, like, all smiles.

10:01.634 --> 10:03.674
Just a little tension
in the air, huh?

10:04.170 --> 10:07.550
It was like Masterpiece Theater.
You know, everyone was so polite.

10:07.607 --> 10:09.807
So they were putting on a
good face for the hired help?

10:09.876 --> 10:13.286
Well, for the children. Both
of them love the kids a lot.

10:13.346 --> 10:15.256
Anything special
happen last night?

10:15.315 --> 10:17.055
Jessica was upset
when I got there.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.597
She wouldn't eat
any of her Jell-Jo.,

10:18.651 --> 10:20.191
and I always give her
Jell-Jo. Before bed.

10:20.253 --> 10:23.393
What was she upset about? Well,
she said she had a tummy ache.

10:23.456 --> 10:26.026
How about Mom and Dad?
How were they feeling?

10:26.893 --> 10:31.343
He wasn't there, actually. And she
just said she was going to a meeting.

10:31.397 --> 10:33.777
And then at about 9:00,
she called

10:33.833 --> 10:36.783
and she said she'd be at her
sister's if I needed anything.

10:36.836 --> 10:39.316
This sister, she lives on
Riverside Drive, doesn't she?

10:39.372 --> 10:40.942
I... I think so.

10:41.007 --> 10:43.037
And...
And then at about 10:00,

10:43.109 --> 10:44.419
Mr. Dobson called

10:44.477 --> 10:47.077
and he wanted to know if his
wife was home yet, and I said,

10:47.147 --> 10:50.417
"No, she's at her sister's,"
and he just hung up.

10:51.918 --> 10:55.918
She left my apartment about 11:00. I
should have walked her to the car.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.659
I watched her from the window,
but there was a tree in the way.

10:58.725 --> 11:01.035
Did you see anyone else on the
street besides your sister?

11:01.094 --> 11:04.374
There was a man in a white
jacket on the other sidewalk.

11:04.430 --> 11:06.540
Did you get a look at his face?
No.

11:07.667 --> 11:11.507
Race? Age? Height? Anything?
I'm sorry.

11:12.605 --> 11:14.515
And you didn't hear a gunshot?

11:15.141 --> 11:17.711
I went into the bedroom
and turned on the television.

11:18.711 --> 11:23.291
The doctor said she might not ever wake up.
The bullet's still inside her.

11:24.617 --> 11:26.027
Ma'am...

11:28.888 --> 11:32.998
I'm gonna ask you to be
as honest as you can be.

11:33.927 --> 11:36.767
How were things going
in your sister's marriage?

11:37.096 --> 11:38.266
What does that matter?

11:38.331 --> 11:40.941
Well, in a case like this,
we have to be very thorough.

11:41.000 --> 11:42.950
But if it was a mugger...

11:47.006 --> 11:49.106
It wasn't a mugger, was it?

11:52.312 --> 11:53.522
He hit her.

11:56.249 --> 11:59.889
She wanted a divorce, but she was afraid.
Afraid of him?

12:00.587 --> 12:03.857
He told he'd fight her for the children.
He had some money hidden somewhere.

12:04.023 --> 12:06.063
He said he'd spend
all of it on the lawyers.

12:07.026 --> 12:10.996
He said she was a bad mother because
she worked a few hours a week.

12:11.064 --> 12:13.514
Nobody loved their children
more than Sandy.

12:14.367 --> 12:18.207
You ever see him hit her? She
never told me, but I knew it.

12:19.172 --> 12:22.212
How many times can you
accidentally walk into a door?

12:24.911 --> 12:27.621
I got a couple of new
questions for Mr. Dobson.

12:27.680 --> 12:29.920
Yeah, I guess it's about time.

12:29.983 --> 12:31.963
What, are you afraid
of hurting his feelings?

12:32.018 --> 12:34.088
Hey, maybe he shot his wife,
but it's just possible

12:34.153 --> 12:37.333
he's just a grieving husband whose
wife was shot by somebody else.

12:37.390 --> 12:39.870
If he's grieving so much, how
come he ain't at the hospital?

12:39.926 --> 12:43.496
He doesn't like doctors?
Let's see how he likes cops.

12:49.168 --> 12:50.908
Watch he doesn't
eat the crayons, huh?

12:58.044 --> 13:00.184
Did you find out
who shot my wife?

13:00.246 --> 13:03.816
No, but we did find that you've been
a little less than honest with us

13:03.883 --> 13:05.293
about last night.

13:05.752 --> 13:06.752
Excuse me?

13:06.819 --> 13:08.729
Well, you told us
your wife was working,

13:08.788 --> 13:11.428
but you didn't say that she
was visiting her sister.

13:13.493 --> 13:16.033
What does it matter
who she was visiting

13:16.095 --> 13:18.905
before she got shot
by some scum on the street?

13:18.965 --> 13:22.805
Yeah, but you also didn't tell us
that your wife wanted a divorce.

13:25.004 --> 13:26.354
(LAUGHING)

13:27.273 --> 13:31.283
Did her sister tell you that?
She's not exactly my biggest fan.

13:31.344 --> 13:34.454
Oh, so everything's been perfect
between you and Mrs. Dobson, huh?

13:34.514 --> 13:36.934
No, everything's normal.

13:36.983 --> 13:39.053
This is a marriage, not a
Barney the Dinosaur song.

13:39.118 --> 13:40.218
We've had our differences.

13:40.286 --> 13:43.026
Like about her working? Yes.
The children need her at home.

13:43.089 --> 13:46.729
Oh, so you thought you'd convince
her to stay home by slugging her?

13:48.628 --> 13:52.078
You guys got the full party
line, didn't you? LOGAN: Yeah.

13:52.131 --> 13:54.341
We saw the bruises
on your wife's body.

13:57.670 --> 13:58.940
You know something?

13:59.605 --> 14:01.545
I don't need you to tell me
I'm a son of a bitch.

14:01.607 --> 14:02.607
Been one for a long time.

14:02.675 --> 14:03.675
I like it, the hours are good

14:03.743 --> 14:04.743
and there's no heavy lifting.

14:04.811 --> 14:06.051
But I happen to be
a son of a bitch

14:06.112 --> 14:09.092
whose wife was shot
by some other son of a bitch.

14:09.515 --> 14:13.155
Mr. Dobson, where were you
at 11:00 last night?

14:16.389 --> 14:18.999
At my club,
listening to bad jokes.

14:20.026 --> 14:21.526
He's here every night.

14:21.594 --> 14:25.244
Has to make sure I don't pour a drink
with an extra millionth of an ounce.

14:25.298 --> 14:28.008
Last night,
was he wearing a white jacket?

14:28.067 --> 14:31.237
Tweed.
His Prince Charles look.

14:31.304 --> 14:34.414
And he was here all night?
Most of the time out here.

14:34.474 --> 14:37.054
Part of the time
in his office, thank God.

14:37.110 --> 14:39.320
You happen to know
when he went into his office?

14:39.879 --> 14:44.229
Off and on. Once right after he called
home from the bar. Asked for his wife.

14:44.283 --> 14:46.663
I don't think she was there.
He got upset.

14:46.719 --> 14:48.719
And where is this office?

14:49.088 --> 14:51.828
Through that curtain, then
the first door on the left.

15:00.666 --> 15:03.036
Well, I guess
this is his office.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.573
And I guess that's an exit.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.380
Well, well, well.

15:09.909 --> 15:13.289
Mr. Dobson could've slipped out anytime
he wanted without saying goodbye.

15:13.346 --> 15:15.286
Yeah, except to his alibi.

15:18.584 --> 15:23.034
Mr. Dobson's the owner of a
registered .32 caliber Seecamp.

15:23.322 --> 15:24.702
Nice gun.

15:24.757 --> 15:28.397
Yeah, and nobody can place him in his
club at the time of the shooting.

15:28.461 --> 15:31.241
No one places him
on Riverside Drive, either.

15:31.297 --> 15:33.497
The sister saw a man
in a white jacket.

15:33.566 --> 15:35.506
You said Dobson
was wearing tweed.

15:35.568 --> 15:37.378
No, the bartender said.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.137
When we saw him
he wasn't wearing a jacket.

15:39.205 --> 15:41.735
Now, why do you think he took it off?
It was hot?

15:41.808 --> 15:43.718
Or splattered with brains.

15:46.579 --> 15:48.249
Tell me the motive again.

15:48.981 --> 15:53.361
How about, she was gonna divorce him,
grab the money, and take his kids?

15:53.419 --> 15:55.229
But did he know that?

15:55.455 --> 15:57.555
She was looking
for a safe deposit box

15:57.623 --> 15:59.193
so she could slap
a court order on it

15:59.258 --> 16:01.258
when she served
the divorce papers.

16:01.327 --> 16:05.277
The whole point of that exercise,
to take it by surprise.

16:08.234 --> 16:09.274
(SIREN WAILING)

16:09.335 --> 16:13.435
Hey, I open an account over there,
I get free checking and a toaster.

16:13.506 --> 16:16.076
A two-slice or a four-slice?
Four-slice.

16:16.142 --> 16:18.752
And if I deposit 50 grand,
I get a VCR.

16:18.811 --> 16:22.421
Hey, if you deposit 50 grand,
I'm calling Internal Affairs.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.992
You get anything?
No, nobody remembers her.

16:25.051 --> 16:28.461
Yeah. I found two places she went
into with a cock-and-bull story

16:28.521 --> 16:31.201
about her husband's safe deposit
box, only he didn't have one.

16:31.257 --> 16:34.167
I had a safe deposit box once.
I gave it up. Why?

16:34.227 --> 16:37.067
After my second divorce I didn't
have anything worth putting in it.

16:37.129 --> 16:39.339
Let's see how her story
plays over here.

16:39.532 --> 16:42.012
She came in, she said she
wanted to rent a box,

16:42.068 --> 16:44.168
and she wanted to know if I
could give her a discount

16:44.237 --> 16:47.547
since her husband had already had a box here.
Or she thought he did.

16:47.607 --> 16:49.777
She seemed to be fishing
for that information?

16:49.842 --> 16:52.122
I just told her she was right
and she was wrong.

16:52.178 --> 16:55.158
Her husband did have a box here, but
I couldn't give her a discount.

16:55.248 --> 16:58.588
I bet she walked out of here whistling.
I wouldn't think so.

16:58.651 --> 17:00.061
But later,
when I talked to the manager,

17:00.119 --> 17:02.859
he said that since Mr. Dobson
was such a good customer

17:02.922 --> 17:06.061
Mrs. Dobson could have
15% off, so I phoned her.

17:06.125 --> 17:09.795
And what did she say? She wasn't home.
I talked to Mr. Dobson.

17:11.696 --> 17:14.176
What did he say?
Nothing really.

17:14.666 --> 17:16.307
Either then
or when I saw him later.

17:16.368 --> 17:19.479
He was in that afternoon,
and he asked to see his box.

17:19.539 --> 17:23.509
He had a small suitcase with him. I
don't think I've seen him since.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.550
CLAIRE: So he knew?

17:25.611 --> 17:28.791
Hey, he hears his old lady's sniffing
around his safe deposit box,

17:28.848 --> 17:31.888
he breaks the four-minute mile
getting to the bank to clear it out.

17:31.951 --> 17:33.061
Okay, right.

17:33.119 --> 17:35.459
But once he's buried the money
where she'll never find it,

17:35.521 --> 17:37.231
his motive to kill her
goes away.

17:37.290 --> 17:39.600
Well, how about the children?
He can't bury them.

17:39.659 --> 17:41.899
He told her he'd fight
for custody and win.

17:41.961 --> 17:43.741
Now, she believed it,
maybe he did, too.

17:43.796 --> 17:46.936
Well, he's gotta know that family
court judges favor mothers.

17:46.999 --> 17:49.539
Besides, this guy's
been lying to us all along.

17:50.903 --> 17:55.013
It's not enough for an arrest.
Well, how about a search warrant?

17:57.043 --> 17:59.083
I'll go see Judge Walther.

17:59.812 --> 18:02.322
Problems with their marriage,
Miss Kincaid?

18:02.682 --> 18:05.822
You're arguing that's
probable cause for a warrant?

18:05.885 --> 18:09.155
In conjunction with the other evidence
uncovered by the officers, yes.

18:09.222 --> 18:12.292
If I allowed the police to
search the home of every man

18:12.358 --> 18:17.308
who owns a gun, hides money from his
wife, and doesn't love her anymore,

18:17.363 --> 18:19.213
there'd be a line
around this courthouse.

18:19.265 --> 18:21.365
Not all those men
hit their wives.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.244
Mrs. Dobson told her sister
she was afraid.

18:23.302 --> 18:24.472
So says the sister.

18:24.537 --> 18:26.777
Your Honor may rely on hearsay
in support of the warrant.

18:26.839 --> 18:29.679
This is double hearsay.
People v. Simon.

18:29.742 --> 18:32.052
Probable cause can be based
on double hearsay.

18:32.111 --> 18:34.521
If it is sufficiently reliable.

18:34.580 --> 18:37.930
With all due respect, Your Honor, should
he receive the benefit of the doubt

18:37.984 --> 18:41.234
because she can't tell you
herself how afraid she was?

18:45.491 --> 18:49.101
TouchÃ©, Miss Kincaid.
Just what I would have argued.

18:51.831 --> 18:53.441
(POLICE RADIO CHATTERING)

18:53.499 --> 18:56.379
MICHAEL: What's going on here?
Stay there.

18:59.005 --> 19:00.635
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

19:00.706 --> 19:02.576
The search warrant's
on the coffee table.

19:02.642 --> 19:05.652
You have no right to be doing this.
BRISCOE: Actually, we do.

19:05.711 --> 19:09.021
With no notice,
in front of my children?

19:09.081 --> 19:12.551
Mr. Dobson, why don't you just...
You are going to be very sorry.

19:13.653 --> 19:17.503
Oh, really? Why?
Are you gonna use this on me?

19:18.557 --> 19:19.587
That gun is registered.

19:19.659 --> 19:21.759
I'd have brought it down if
you'd just asked me for it.

19:21.827 --> 19:24.307
Do you own a white jacket,
Mr. Dobson?

19:27.800 --> 19:31.810
What about this? Were you
wearing this the other night?

19:33.839 --> 19:35.279
That's why you got
the search warrant?

19:35.341 --> 19:38.151
Looks like you're taking it to the cleaners.
Can you tell me why?

19:39.412 --> 19:43.262
Because it's dirty?
This is unbelievable.

19:43.916 --> 19:49.086
Very practical. Tweed, it
conceals a multitude of sins.

19:49.555 --> 19:54.495
Like attempted murder? Like spilled gravy.
Fresh. Smell.

19:56.862 --> 19:59.902
Whole thing smells like chemicals to me.
It's phenolphthalein.

19:59.965 --> 20:02.405
I'm sorry, I forgot.
I'm so used to it.

20:02.468 --> 20:04.378
I used it
to raise the blood stains.

20:04.437 --> 20:07.177
Type Jo..
It matches Mrs. Dobson's.

20:07.239 --> 20:10.049
Yeah, and about 45%
of the general population.

20:10.109 --> 20:14.289
Well, it is also EAP Type-B, which
matches 40% of the population,

20:14.347 --> 20:18.687
and PGM Type-2, which match
5% of the population.

20:18.985 --> 20:23.225
So you multiply
0.45 x 0.40 x 0.05.

20:23.589 --> 20:27.369
Now the blood in these stains match
less than 1% of the population.

20:27.660 --> 20:31.670
So would that 1% include
Mrs. Dobson? Yes.

20:33.099 --> 20:35.079
BRISCOE: We pulled
your phone records, Dobson.

20:35.134 --> 20:37.174
We know you called
two divorce lawyers

20:37.236 --> 20:39.146
the day you cleaned out
your safe deposit box.

20:39.205 --> 20:41.045
It's a crime to call a lawyer?

20:41.107 --> 20:43.447
Well, you told us
you weren't thinking divorce.

20:43.509 --> 20:44.539
You already had the wrong idea.

20:44.610 --> 20:46.060
I didn't want to
confuse you further.

20:46.112 --> 20:48.922
Michael, I think we should
listen here, not talk.

20:48.981 --> 20:50.521
I'll handle this, Max.

20:50.583 --> 20:54.163
Both divorce lawyers told me I could
get out of the marriage on my terms.

20:54.220 --> 20:55.820
Well, was one of the terms

20:55.888 --> 20:59.128
your wife bleeding on the jacket you
were wearing the night she was shot?

20:59.191 --> 21:02.701
Again with the jacket. I haven't
cleaned that jacket in months.

21:02.762 --> 21:05.272
My wife fell off a bicycle last
spring at our country house.

21:05.331 --> 21:09.441
I helped her up. She fell
or you knocked her down?

21:11.070 --> 21:15.640
Okay, let's say I knocked her down.
What if I punched her?

21:15.908 --> 21:18.678
Does that account for your bloodstain?
Can I go now?

21:19.779 --> 21:22.019
You want to tell us again why
nobody saw you in your club

21:22.081 --> 21:25.191
around the time your wife was shot?
Come on, Dobson, the place...

21:25.251 --> 21:27.091
If he gave her a bloody nose
six months ago,

21:27.153 --> 21:29.133
we can't tie the bloodstain
to the shooting.

21:29.188 --> 21:32.928
So he gets away with attempted
murder because he's a wife beater?

21:33.259 --> 21:37.609
What a smug bastard. Don't you want to
lock him up just on general principles?

21:37.663 --> 21:38.773
Yeah.

21:39.732 --> 21:45.442
The blood, the prints,
no alibi, past abuse, the gun,

21:45.504 --> 21:49.424
the divorce, the safe deposit
box, and his personality.

21:50.676 --> 21:52.346
That's enough for a grand jury,

21:52.745 --> 21:54.185
and it might shake
Mr. Dobson up

21:54.246 --> 21:56.746
if we put someone
in control of him for awhile.

21:57.016 --> 21:58.386
Yes, ma'am.

21:59.385 --> 22:00.725
MICHAEL: Let's go.
This is getting monotonous.

22:00.786 --> 22:02.786
Michael Dobson,
you're under arrest

22:02.855 --> 22:04.525
for the attempted murder
of Sandra Dobson.

22:04.590 --> 22:05.970
You have the right
to remain silent.

22:06.025 --> 22:08.935
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

22:11.697 --> 22:16.107
"Docket number 64029.
People v. Michael Dobson."

22:16.168 --> 22:18.008
"Attempted murder
in the Second Degree."

22:18.237 --> 22:20.807
JUDGE BERMAN: How does he plead?
Not guilty.

22:20.873 --> 22:23.913
The People request bail in the amount
of one million dollars, Your Honor.

22:23.976 --> 22:28.356
That is clearly punitive. Mr. Dobson
owns a business in New York.

22:28.414 --> 22:29.454
He has children.

22:29.515 --> 22:32.925
And the woman he intended
to kill is here. Alive.

22:33.219 --> 22:36.259
The People believe Mr. Dobson
remains a threat to her.

22:36.755 --> 22:38.755
Have I been convicted
of something?

22:38.824 --> 22:41.504
No, sir, but we'd like to
see you for your trial.

22:41.694 --> 22:43.504
500,000 cash or bond.

22:44.430 --> 22:46.500
I've seen stronger cases.

22:46.565 --> 22:49.165
Hey, if the guy had shot her
in Times Square at rush hour,

22:49.235 --> 22:50.935
we'd have brought you
a stronger case.

22:51.003 --> 22:52.643
No witnesses?

22:52.705 --> 22:56.275
We canvassed that neighborhood three times.
No one saw Dobson.

22:56.342 --> 22:58.382
And we're working
on the taxi records now,

22:58.444 --> 23:00.154
in case he took a cab
there from his club.

23:00.212 --> 23:01.692
JACK: No shell casings?

23:02.448 --> 23:04.548
Dobson's gun is an automatic,
isn't it?

23:04.617 --> 23:06.997
Well, he's no dummy.
Maybe he picked it up.

23:07.319 --> 23:10.699
He could've picked it up. That'll
go over well in cross-examination.

23:11.157 --> 23:14.867
You didn't talk to Dobson's daughter?
The seven-year-old?

23:14.927 --> 23:17.967
The babysitter said that she was
upset the night of the shooting.

23:18.564 --> 23:19.574
Before the shooting.

23:19.632 --> 23:23.012
The babysitter said she had a stomachache,
and we had other things to do.

23:23.068 --> 23:26.238
Like establish Dobson's
motive and destroy his alibi.

23:26.305 --> 23:29.245
You couldn't go back later and find
out why she had a stomachache?

23:29.308 --> 23:31.618
LOGAN: You think you know
so much about being a cop?

23:31.677 --> 23:35.177
Why don't you do the investigating?
Are you giving me attitude?

23:35.447 --> 23:37.387
My father was a cop
for 31 years,

23:37.449 --> 23:40.989
and he would never leave a DA
twisting with a half-made case

23:41.053 --> 23:42.433
and ask him
to get an indictment.

23:42.488 --> 23:44.898
Give me a break. You could
get a ham sandwich indicted.

23:44.957 --> 23:47.837
That might be easier. There's
meat on a ham sandwich.

23:49.762 --> 23:51.572
We'll go see the kid.

23:52.031 --> 23:54.101
JACK: Just the taxi records,
please.

23:54.433 --> 23:56.573
I think Claire will be fine
with the kid.

24:04.410 --> 24:07.410
I've given the children the bedroom.
The couch pulls out.

24:07.780 --> 24:11.090
I'd really like to speak with Jessica.
Well, can't it wait?

24:11.150 --> 24:15.120
All she knows is that her mother is sick.
She should be asleep by now.

24:15.187 --> 24:18.187
Aunt Kathleen?
Oh, what is it, honey?

24:18.257 --> 24:20.497
Jeremy's having
a nightmare again.

24:20.559 --> 24:23.199
Well, I'll look in on him
in a minute.

24:25.030 --> 24:27.510
This is Miss Kincaid, honey.
Claire.

24:27.566 --> 24:31.166
She's a friend of your Mommy's.
She wants to ask you a question.

24:31.303 --> 24:33.483
CLAIRE: It's about the night
your mom got sick.

24:34.139 --> 24:37.519
Your babysitter, Susannah, said
you were unhappy about something.

24:37.943 --> 24:39.513
What was it, Jessica?

24:40.346 --> 24:44.156
It's okay, honey. Mommy
said it was okay to say.

24:46.318 --> 24:48.728
Mommy and Daddy had a fight.

24:50.122 --> 24:52.032
Do you remember what they said?

24:52.091 --> 24:54.901
Why can't I see Mommy?
Oh.

24:56.962 --> 24:59.502
Do you remember what the
fight was about, honey?

25:00.499 --> 25:03.039
Daddy didn't want her
to go out.

25:05.404 --> 25:07.014
What did he say?

25:08.073 --> 25:12.043
He was angry, like when
we do something wrong.

25:12.678 --> 25:15.018
Does he get angry at you,
honey?

25:15.748 --> 25:17.348
Does he ever hurt you?

25:17.549 --> 25:19.149
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

25:23.622 --> 25:25.802
KATHLEEN: Michael...
MICHAEL: Get out of my way.

25:25.858 --> 25:28.068
Hey...
Daddy!

25:28.127 --> 25:29.467
Okay, honey, get your brother.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.568
KATHLEEN: What are you doing here?
It's called bail.

25:31.630 --> 25:33.870
I'm sure Miss Kincaid
can explain it to you.

25:33.933 --> 25:37.613
You're not taking these children.
Oh, yes, I am. Jessica, now!

25:37.970 --> 25:40.540
Okay. Hey, come here,
big guy. All righty.

25:40.606 --> 25:44.916
Stop him. I'm their father.
You just try it.

25:45.377 --> 25:48.947
How can you let him get away with this?
There's nothing I can do.

25:49.381 --> 25:53.691
Is this how you win a custody battle?
Just shoot the children's mother?

25:55.287 --> 25:56.357
God.

25:59.625 --> 26:03.595
He shot my sister. God only knows
what he might do to the children.

26:04.296 --> 26:06.396
CLAIRE: I checked with their
doctor and local hospitals.

26:06.465 --> 26:09.375
There have been no reports
suggestive of child abuse.

26:11.537 --> 26:14.017
Did you ever see him
abusing the children?

26:15.207 --> 26:17.517
Did your sister ever tell you
that he abused them?

26:17.576 --> 26:19.816
He shot their mother.
Isn't that abuse?

26:19.878 --> 26:22.448
Legally? No.

26:23.982 --> 26:28.092
There was a case called
O'Guin v. Pikul.

26:28.153 --> 26:31.833
In it, the judge ruled that a father
has a right to keep his own children.

26:31.890 --> 26:33.930
That he strangled his wife
was irrelevant.

26:33.992 --> 26:36.802
If we had evidence your brother-in-law
I left Jessica and Jeremy

26:36.862 --> 26:40.372
alone for ten minutes while he
went out to buy a newspaper,

26:40.432 --> 26:42.942
that would demonstrate
unfitness as a parent.

26:43.001 --> 26:44.981
And trying
to kill their mother?

26:45.037 --> 26:47.637
Not unless he did it
in front of the children.

26:51.343 --> 26:53.883
Miss O'Brien
is unhappy with the law.

26:55.080 --> 26:59.190
Another satisfied customer. She's
petitioning for custody anyway.

26:59.351 --> 27:00.831
She'll lose.

27:00.886 --> 27:04.456
Well, what if we intervene on her side?
In civil court?

27:04.523 --> 27:06.803
We have a witness to protect
from undue influence.

27:06.859 --> 27:10.709
Some witness. A seven-year-old
who loves her father,

27:11.463 --> 27:16.073
and overheard an adult conversation that
she may or may not have understood.

27:16.268 --> 27:20.268
She heard her father arguing with her
mother a few hours before she was shot.

27:20.706 --> 27:24.776
And I'm sure her father has already
persuaded her to remember it differently.

27:24.843 --> 27:27.953
Want to try to turn the law around?
Be my guest.

27:28.247 --> 27:31.187
Just don't complain to me
you're overworked.

27:35.721 --> 27:40.431
Miss Kincaid, I'm sure that Miss O'Brien's
counsel is fully capable of arguing

27:40.492 --> 27:42.532
her claim of custody
to these children.

27:42.594 --> 27:43.664
He is, Your Honor.

27:43.729 --> 27:47.539
But the People have a separate interest
here relating to a criminal prosecution.

27:47.599 --> 27:50.549
A prosecution that has
no bearing on this preceding.

27:50.602 --> 27:53.642
The People intend to call
Jessica Dobson as a witness.

27:53.705 --> 27:57.735
Her testimony may be contaminated if she
continues to reside with the defendant.

27:57.809 --> 28:01.119
A suitable home with Miss O'Brien
is available until the trial.

28:01.180 --> 28:04.060
Your Honor, may I speak, please?
Briefly.

28:05.651 --> 28:09.621
Jessica and Jeremy have been with
me every day of their lives.

28:09.688 --> 28:11.858
We are a very close family.

28:11.924 --> 28:15.464
To take them away from me now,
after they've lost their mother...

28:15.527 --> 28:17.227
CLAIRE: Your Honor,
this is outrageous.

28:17.296 --> 28:20.396
The People contend they only lost
their mother because he shot her.

28:20.465 --> 28:21.765
Miss Kincaid.

28:21.833 --> 28:25.473
To take them from me now would
be emotionally devastating.

28:25.537 --> 28:29.917
I appeal to you as a father, please let
my children stay where they belong.

28:31.510 --> 28:32.820
Your Honor.

28:35.547 --> 28:39.287
Miss Kincaid, I have
interviewed the girl. Alone.

28:39.918 --> 28:41.828
She seems genuinely fond
of her father.

28:41.887 --> 28:45.027
That's not the immediate issue
here, begging the court's pardon.

28:45.090 --> 28:46.540
You're forgiven.

28:47.292 --> 28:49.672
I asked Jessica about the
night her mother was shot.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.208
She says she remembers nothing.

28:51.263 --> 28:54.713
She told me her parents argued.
That's not what she says now.

28:54.766 --> 28:58.336
Because her father's manipulated her.
Or she's telling the truth.

28:58.403 --> 29:01.683
Either way, Miss Kincaid,
it makes your motion moot.

29:01.907 --> 29:04.007
You don't have
much of a witness there.

29:04.443 --> 29:07.653
We'll proceed on Miss O'Brien's
petition for custody.

29:11.116 --> 29:12.956
God. Her father got to her.

29:14.052 --> 29:15.832
So let's get to him.

29:16.221 --> 29:19.261
How? Did the police miss something else?
The bullet.

29:19.558 --> 29:22.098
We haven't tried to match it
to Dobson's gun.

29:22.528 --> 29:25.338
The bullet is inside
Mrs. Dobson's brain.

29:26.832 --> 29:28.512
So let's get it out.

29:34.506 --> 29:36.606
CLAIRE: The bullet's intact?
GEORGE: It seems to be.

29:36.675 --> 29:39.845
And it's .32 caliber?
It seems to be.

29:40.813 --> 29:43.953
You can't seriously expect us to dig
around next to a patient's brainstem

29:44.016 --> 29:45.646
so you can run some tests?

29:45.717 --> 29:47.587
What are you planning to do?

29:47.653 --> 29:50.793
She's entered a vegetative
state, probably irreversible.

29:51.223 --> 29:55.143
The bullet is blocking the flow of spinal
fluid, causing acute hydrocephalus.

29:55.427 --> 29:57.457
So it might make sense
to remove the bullet.

29:57.529 --> 30:00.199
It makes better sense to install a
shunt between the fourth ventricle

30:00.265 --> 30:02.905
and the peritoneum, which would
allow the fluid to drain.

30:02.968 --> 30:04.968
Well,
if you're operating anyway.

30:05.037 --> 30:07.107
Removing the bullet
might help her.

30:07.172 --> 30:10.052
But putting in a shunt is a
lot less likely to kill her.

30:11.743 --> 30:13.883
Dobson had his lawyer
call the hospital.

30:14.613 --> 30:16.623
He's given permission
for the shunt operation,

30:16.682 --> 30:19.362
but refused it
for the removal of the bullet.

30:19.418 --> 30:22.228
He said he's concerned
about his wife's well-being.

30:23.255 --> 30:25.325
Like he was when he shot her.

30:25.390 --> 30:26.890
Well, he might be right
this time.

30:26.958 --> 30:28.838
Removing the bullet
is dangerous.

30:30.529 --> 30:32.439
You said there was no hope
of recovery.

30:32.497 --> 30:35.877
The doctor said
it was probably irreversible.

30:37.436 --> 30:40.776
Removing the bullet increases
the chances of recovery.

30:40.839 --> 30:43.479
It also increases
the chance of death.

30:43.742 --> 30:46.522
Okay, three things can happen.

30:46.945 --> 30:50.685
She gets better, she stays
the same, or she dies.

30:51.183 --> 30:54.223
One out of three, she dies?
I don't like the odds.

30:54.286 --> 30:56.856
Two out of three, she's no
worse off than she was before,

30:56.922 --> 30:59.272
and we get crucial evidence.

31:01.026 --> 31:02.506
I don't know.

31:04.463 --> 31:09.213
We let her husband walk so she can spend
the rest of her life as a vegetable?

31:10.102 --> 31:12.512
You think
that's the right thing to do?

31:13.238 --> 31:15.118
I'll draft the motion.

31:19.077 --> 31:20.847
WESTON: The law is explicit.

31:20.912 --> 31:25.292
The state may not compel the removal of
alleged evidence from a person's body

31:25.350 --> 31:28.800
if doing so creates a risk
of serious physical injury.

31:29.254 --> 31:31.334
That law applies
to criminal suspects

31:31.390 --> 31:33.630
who decline to give their
consent to the procedure.

31:33.692 --> 31:37.002
Nothing prevents a victim
from consenting voluntarily.

31:37.062 --> 31:39.472
As I understand it,
this particular victim

31:39.531 --> 31:41.571
is incapable
of making a decision.

31:41.633 --> 31:45.983
Exactly. Therefore, the only issue
here is who shall make it for her.

31:46.038 --> 31:48.988
That's well established.
The next of kin, her husband.

31:49.041 --> 31:52.721
Mr. Dobson has an insurmountable
conflict of interest here.

31:52.778 --> 31:55.188
Miss O'Brien,
the victim's sister, does not.

31:55.247 --> 32:00.527
Your Honor, Miss O'Brien has demonstrated
a clear animus toward Mr. Dobson.

32:00.585 --> 32:02.715
JACK: But not toward
Mrs. Dobson.

32:02.788 --> 32:04.388
She's a loving
and devoted sister,

32:04.456 --> 32:06.896
who intends to be guided
by the victim's own wishes

32:06.958 --> 32:09.798
as expressed in a living will
she prepared two years ago.

32:09.861 --> 32:11.571
I've examined the document.

32:11.630 --> 32:15.340
It asks that Mrs. Dobson not be
kept alive by mechanical means.

32:15.400 --> 32:16.670
Now, is that the case here?

32:16.735 --> 32:19.905
She's being fed through a tube.
She's breathing on her own.

32:19.971 --> 32:24.281
All we ask is that someone
not accused of shooting her

32:24.342 --> 32:26.622
be empowered
to make the decision.

32:27.612 --> 32:29.722
That does seem reasonable.

32:30.949 --> 32:34.059
The hospital will be notified
that for purposes of decisions

32:34.119 --> 32:36.759
regarding Sandra Dobson's
medical care,

32:36.822 --> 32:40.292
her sister shall be regarded
as de jure next of kin.

32:40.592 --> 32:42.072
(GAVEL POUNDING)

32:46.064 --> 32:48.704
Well, I understand
you've been promoted

32:48.767 --> 32:52.437
from Assistant District
Attorney to supreme deity.

32:53.839 --> 32:56.479
I'm not making the decision.
It's up to the sister.

32:56.541 --> 33:02.011
Oh, you're just a casual bystander who
just happened to find himself arguing

33:02.080 --> 33:05.550
against the husband's right
to manage his wife's life.

33:06.485 --> 33:09.585
He does have a conflict of interest.
And you don't?

33:11.089 --> 33:16.229
Isn't justice in Mrs. Dobson's interest, too?
I don't know the woman.

33:16.661 --> 33:19.871
But she might be more
interested in staying alive.

33:33.178 --> 33:35.158
(MACHINE BEEPING)

33:39.951 --> 33:43.191
I'm ready. Where's the paper?
CLAIRE: Here.

33:43.655 --> 33:45.995
I do not recommend
this surgery.

33:46.591 --> 33:50.041
Can you tell me my sister will
come back to me without it?

33:59.871 --> 34:01.441
It's up to you.

34:15.754 --> 34:18.634
Sandra Dobson
died on the operating table.

34:24.963 --> 34:26.072
And?

34:28.500 --> 34:32.000
They got the bullet. It
doesn't match Dobson's gun.

34:41.846 --> 34:43.116
Claire...

34:44.882 --> 34:46.693
Amend the indictment.

34:48.853 --> 34:50.274
Murder two.

34:54.659 --> 34:58.129
Congratulations on killing
my client's wife, Mr. McCoy.

34:58.897 --> 35:02.997
Are you sure the murder charge doesn't
involve a little projection on your part?

35:03.068 --> 35:06.348
Come on, Max.
People v. Bonilla.

35:06.404 --> 35:09.444
Even if the surgery was
ill-advised, which it wasn't,

35:10.041 --> 35:12.251
the person who put her in the
hospital in the first place

35:12.310 --> 35:13.520
is responsible for her death.

35:13.578 --> 35:15.918
Yeah,
but that's not Mr. Dobson.

35:16.348 --> 35:18.288
Haven't you read
your own ballistics report?

35:18.350 --> 35:19.350
Yes.

35:19.951 --> 35:24.531
It says he didn't shoot her with the
gun the police found in his apartment.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.704
Does your client
own any other guns?

35:29.294 --> 35:34.944
Please. Time to cut your losses, Jack.
See you in court.

35:44.242 --> 35:47.522
A second gun?
They have a country house.

35:47.579 --> 35:50.359
Yeah, the house was searched.
What about the country?

35:50.415 --> 35:53.355
Excuse me? The house
is in Dutchess County.

35:53.418 --> 35:57.258
Have them check every gun dealer
within a 100-mile radius,

35:57.656 --> 36:00.026
including Connecticut
and Massachusetts.

36:06.364 --> 36:08.174
JACK: Where do you work,
Mr. Harding?

36:08.233 --> 36:11.113
Jack's Sporting Goods,
Bridgeport, Connecticut.

36:11.469 --> 36:15.979
Bridgeport? That's not too far from
the New York state line, is it?

36:16.041 --> 36:18.251
We get some customers
from there.

36:19.511 --> 36:22.051
Why would they drive
the extra miles?

36:22.113 --> 36:24.653
Well,
they could be sightseeing.

36:25.550 --> 36:29.400
Or the gun laws. They're a little
tougher in New York than Connecticut.

36:31.223 --> 36:34.143
Do you recognize
the defendant, Michael Dobson?

36:34.759 --> 36:37.169
HARDING: He's been in.
JACK: Sightseeing?

36:37.229 --> 36:40.179
Well, I don't know.
But he bought a gun.

36:40.231 --> 36:44.271
Was it a .32 caliber Seecamp? It
was a .32, but not a Seecamp.

36:45.804 --> 36:48.314
Are you sure about that?
It's my business.

36:48.807 --> 36:53.217
He bought a Ruger revolver,
$298. Nice little gun.

36:54.579 --> 36:56.389
JACK: No further questions.

36:57.248 --> 37:00.788
Trying to find his safe deposit
box, that was my idea.

37:01.353 --> 37:03.893
I read it in a magazine
and told Sandy.

37:03.955 --> 37:07.485
After your sister had located her
husband's box, what did she do?

37:07.559 --> 37:08.799
Nothing.

37:08.860 --> 37:12.430
I told her it was time to
move, to file the papers,

37:13.331 --> 37:14.831
but she was terrified
of Michael.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.740
Move to strike, Your Honor.

37:16.801 --> 37:18.441
Miss O'Brien
is not a mind-reader,

37:18.503 --> 37:20.453
and anything her sister
told her is hearsay.

37:20.505 --> 37:22.875
Your Honor,
sisters are certainly capable

37:22.941 --> 37:24.391
of interpreting
each other's moods.

37:25.744 --> 37:29.324
I'll allow that. But keep
Mrs. Dobson's words out of it.

37:31.082 --> 37:33.322
How did your sister act,
Miss O'Brien?

37:33.852 --> 37:37.362
If I mentioned Michael's name,
I could see her get all tight.

37:39.290 --> 37:41.170
Ever since
she was a little girl,

37:41.226 --> 37:45.636
she used to twirl her hair
when she would get upset.

37:47.365 --> 37:49.935
A few months ago I noticed
she was pulling hairs out.

37:50.001 --> 37:53.451
I showed her. After that
she wore her hair up.

37:54.372 --> 37:57.112
When was the last time
you talked to Mr. Dobson?

37:57.175 --> 38:00.645
After the custody hearing. I
wanted to visit the children.

38:00.712 --> 38:02.252
You called him?

38:04.516 --> 38:07.586
He told me if I tried
to see the children again,

38:07.652 --> 38:09.432
he would make me regret it.

38:09.621 --> 38:12.121
That I ought to know by now he
knew how to take care of people

38:12.190 --> 38:14.800
who tried to take
his children away from him.

38:16.795 --> 38:20.735
And you took that as a threat? Of course.
He shot my sister.

38:20.799 --> 38:23.079
Move to strike.
Non-responsive.

38:23.134 --> 38:25.444
Sustained.
Jury will disregard.

38:27.338 --> 38:28.938
No further questions.

38:32.944 --> 38:37.094
So you're saying
that despite the fact

38:37.148 --> 38:40.648
your sister never took any
step toward getting a divorce,

38:41.853 --> 38:46.603
you could tell that she wanted to
because she changed her hairstyle?

38:46.891 --> 38:50.771
She told me she wanted one.
I see. Really?

38:51.830 --> 38:57.640
Miss O'Brien, aren't you desperate
to see Mr. Dobson convicted

38:58.336 --> 39:00.646
because you feel guilty?
No.

39:00.705 --> 39:05.745
Because, over his objection, you ordered an
operation that led to your sister's death?

39:05.810 --> 39:08.350
The doctor said it might relieve
the pressure on her brain.

39:08.413 --> 39:12.123
The doctors advised you
not to have the operation.

39:12.183 --> 39:14.723
I couldn't let him get away with it.
I see.

39:15.920 --> 39:18.630
Now as for this alleged threat.

39:20.091 --> 39:25.171
Didn't Mr. Dobson merely ask to be allowed
to live in peace with his own children?

39:25.230 --> 39:28.300
In peace? What did he do to
Jessica to make her lie?

39:28.366 --> 39:30.896
Miss O'Brien... In front of
the baby he threatened Sandy

39:30.969 --> 39:32.139
the same way he threatened me.

39:32.203 --> 39:34.213
Miss O'Brien, that'll be enough.
They should know!

39:38.643 --> 39:42.063
Impassioned relatives,
they do impress a jury.

39:42.113 --> 39:43.523
The gun helps, too.

39:43.581 --> 39:46.531
Suggesting the possibility
that Dobson shot her

39:46.584 --> 39:49.794
without putting you to the trouble
of running another ballistics test,

39:49.854 --> 39:52.464
unless you're unlucky enough
to find the gun.

39:52.524 --> 39:54.534
If they find it, it will match.

39:54.592 --> 39:57.902
Dobson's claiming it was
stolen a year ago. Convenient.

39:57.962 --> 40:00.072
I think the jury
will see it that way.

40:00.465 --> 40:02.465
(PHONE RINGING)

40:04.536 --> 40:05.736
Yes?

40:07.105 --> 40:09.085
Detective Logan. Urgent.

40:09.941 --> 40:12.511
Yeah, he was picked up
with a knife in Alphabet City

40:12.577 --> 40:16.487
after two drug tourists from
Jersey got stabbed last week.

40:16.815 --> 40:18.485
So he spent the next day
at the One-Five,

40:18.550 --> 40:22.760
he got shipped to Central Booking, then
Rikers, then he got lost for 48 hours

40:22.821 --> 40:25.031
until somebody listened to his
story and mailed him here.

40:25.090 --> 40:26.690
What's he looking at,
assault one?

40:26.758 --> 40:29.708
He prefers
the climate downstate.

40:29.994 --> 40:33.704
Who's out there, your boss? Yeah.
Hi, President Clinton.

40:34.132 --> 40:37.242
Go ahead, tell it. You cut me a
little slack, I give you a killer.

40:37.302 --> 40:41.252
Who we talking about, Joey? Robin.
Like Robin Williams, you know?

40:41.306 --> 40:43.306
The guy is all the time jokey.
It's very annoying.

40:43.374 --> 40:45.124
He one of your customers?

40:46.311 --> 40:50.851
An acquaintance who likes to ride downtown.
Smack express.

40:51.182 --> 40:53.132
When he's not doped up
he's a stick-up kid.

40:53.184 --> 40:55.564
What, armed robberies?
Yeah.

40:55.620 --> 40:58.000
Couple of months ago, he has
this party at his place.

40:58.056 --> 41:01.366
Heroin for him, beer for anybody
else who can climb the stairs.

41:01.426 --> 41:02.836
Told me he was celebrating.

41:02.894 --> 41:06.214
Told me he took off some lady
in Riverside Drive in a BMW.

41:06.698 --> 41:08.078
That ring any bells with you?

41:08.132 --> 41:11.012
Did you see
any of this lady's stuff?

41:11.069 --> 41:12.909
Yeah, he's waving around
a purple scarf.

41:12.971 --> 41:15.651
Told me he was gonna save it for
after his sex-change operation.

41:15.707 --> 41:19.087
He was talking, like,
"Hello, Joseph." Annoying.

41:20.478 --> 41:24.478
I don't believe this.
It's your call, Counselors.

41:26.417 --> 41:30.827
She had on a beige dress. What does
it matter what she was wearing?

41:31.723 --> 41:35.033
When your sister left here, did
she have any kind of scarf?

41:35.960 --> 41:38.530
Yes. Silk. Mauve.

41:40.632 --> 41:43.642
Oh, it wasn't with her clothes
at the hospital. Do you have it?

41:43.701 --> 41:46.111
Mauve.
That's like purple, right?

41:48.506 --> 41:50.036
Does Michael have it?

41:54.646 --> 41:56.816
Does someone else have it?

41:57.615 --> 41:59.385
We don't know that.

42:01.986 --> 42:03.396
Oh, my God.

42:04.689 --> 42:06.789
I killed Sandy for nothing.

42:10.094 --> 42:11.704
Police! Open up!

42:11.763 --> 42:12.973
(BABY CRYING)

42:14.165 --> 42:16.265
You're gonna have to
knock louder than that.

42:16.334 --> 42:21.614
A junkie named Robin? Not anymore.
He died Tuesday. Hepatitis.

42:23.274 --> 42:25.984
These people don't take care
of themselves.

42:27.979 --> 42:30.189
Is all this his stuff?
Mmm-hmm.

42:31.449 --> 42:34.949
What did he do, knock off a video store?
Well, he liked TV.

42:35.820 --> 42:37.820
This is my Christmas tip.

42:38.022 --> 42:41.272
The rest I don't even want to touch.
I'm getting it cleaned tomorrow.

42:41.326 --> 42:43.566
Yeah, well, we get first dibs.

42:45.263 --> 42:46.903
LOGAN: Look at this.

42:47.865 --> 42:49.305
BRISCOE:
What do you got there?

42:51.202 --> 42:52.682
White jacket.

42:56.541 --> 42:58.951
How exactly
do you get hepatitis?

42:59.277 --> 43:02.047
He kept this nice and clean.
.32.

43:04.082 --> 43:05.892
That's not a Ruger.
No, Colt.

43:08.920 --> 43:12.270
You don't think we're gonna owe
Dobson an apology, do you?

43:12.323 --> 43:14.393
I hope Hallmark
makes the right card.

43:14.459 --> 43:17.669
American Express and Visa.
Sandra Dobson.

43:26.437 --> 43:30.007
"In the light of new information
developed by the police,"

43:30.074 --> 43:33.154
"the People withdraw the charge
against Michael Dobson."

43:33.645 --> 43:36.745
The charge is dismissed.
Bail is exonerated.

43:36.814 --> 43:41.064
You're free to go, sir. Thank you, Your Honor.
Thank you, Max.

43:41.119 --> 43:43.659
I'm glad this is over. You're
still not worth the money.

43:43.721 --> 43:47.071
No? Come on.
Come on, let's get a drink.

43:51.462 --> 43:55.882
I've never been in this situation.
You'll get over it.

43:57.135 --> 44:01.805
All's well that ends well, huh, McCoy?
I gotta pick up the kids now.

44:02.373 --> 44:05.953
Oh, thanks to you, no alimony.

44:13.551 --> 44:16.561
McCoy! You gotta see this.

44:20.958 --> 44:23.598
I found the tape
in Robin's apartment.

44:24.262 --> 44:27.372
It's a local cable show.
That's Robin.

44:27.432 --> 44:31.042
And there's these cotton balls
at the top of the bottles,

44:31.102 --> 44:34.312
and, like, you know, they're really
useful when you're shooting,

44:34.739 --> 44:36.479
so it drove us nuts.
A junkie comedian?

44:36.541 --> 44:37.951
Ever hear of Lennie Bruce?
Nuts!

44:38.009 --> 44:39.449
Should we save the cotton?

44:39.510 --> 44:40.920
BRISCOE: Lennie Bruce never shot
anybody on Riverside Drive.

44:40.978 --> 44:45.688
I mean, are we really quitting,
or should we save the cotton?

44:46.517 --> 44:49.517
I've seen worse.
Wait. It gets better.

44:49.587 --> 44:51.787
You've been great.

44:51.856 --> 44:53.836
Thanks a lot. Yeah, beat it.
Don't worry about it.

44:53.891 --> 44:55.461
Get out. Scram.
I'll see you all on Avenue C.

44:55.526 --> 44:57.666
Right, yeah. Scram.
Dobson.

44:57.728 --> 44:59.868
Robin Wenner. Give him a nice hand.
Robin Wenner.

44:59.931 --> 45:02.841
LOGAN: They taped the show
at his club a year ago.

45:09.574 --> 45:12.994
Next up on Open Mike Live is...

45:14.645 --> 45:17.085
The police checked
phone records,

45:18.216 --> 45:20.086
Dobson's bank account,

45:21.119 --> 45:24.259
the store where Robin
cashed his welfare checks.

45:26.391 --> 45:30.771
They interviewed Dobson's friends,
Robin's friends, the people at the club.

45:30.828 --> 45:33.568
They couldn't find
any other connection,

45:33.898 --> 45:39.678
meeting, conversation between
Dobson and Robin. Nothing.

45:43.141 --> 45:46.351
You think it's just a coincidence
the killer appeared at a club

45:46.410 --> 45:48.690
owned by the victim's husband?

45:49.647 --> 45:50.677
No.

45:55.086 --> 45:58.556
But even if I could retry him,
I couldn't convict.

45:59.757 --> 46:01.737
He didn't leave a trail.

46:03.027 --> 46:04.197
Smart.

46:07.498 --> 46:08.668
Lucky.

46:10.668 --> 46:12.078
Or innocent.

